<div >
    <div class="sfContentBlock" ><div class="clearfix spacer-40"></div></div>
</div>
<div >
    <div class="sfContentBlock" ><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>World Vision's Syria response</h3><p style="box-sizing:border-box;margin-bottom:11.5px;color:#060000;font-family:Lato, 'Trebuchet MS', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;">World Vision&rsquo;s initial response to the crisis focused on supporting the resettlement and basic needs of Syrian refugees in Lebanon. World Vision is now responding in five countries &ndash; Syria, Lebanon, Jordan, Turkey and Iraq &ndash; and works beyond families&rsquo; basic needs to tackle complex social problems that affect children&rsquo;s rights and individual resilience.<span style="color:#060000;font-family:Lato, 'Trebuchet MS', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;"> In 2018, we provided assistance to 1.2 million people including 700,000 children.</span><span style="color:#060000;font-family:Lato, 'Trebuchet MS', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;">&nbsp;</span></p><p style="box-sizing:border-box;margin-bottom:11.5px;color:#060000;font-family:Lato, 'Trebuchet MS', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;">This assistance included:</p><ul style="box-sizing:border-box;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:11.5px;color:#060000;font-family:Lato, 'Trebuchet MS', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;"><li style="box-sizing:border-box;">helping people access food, clean water, sanitation and hygiene services</li><li style="box-sizing:border-box;">providing shelter and emergency supplies such as blankets, stoves and warm winter clothing</li><li style="box-sizing:border-box;">supporting fractured health systems: hospitals, maternal services, health centres and mobile clinics</li><li style="box-sizing:border-box;">providing safe spaces for children to learn, play and receive other forms of support</li><li style="box-sizing:border-box;">implementing programs addressing children&rsquo;s social interactions, family bonds and psychosocial wellbeing</li><li style="box-sizing:border-box;">supporting bridging courses and additional classes to get children back to school</li></ul><p>Most of the refugee population, especially children, are starting to reclaim their lives and livelihoods through education. To help them reach their goals, we have helped construct schools, rehabilitate education infrastructure, and provide livelihood assistance to severely affected communities.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>
</div><div class="photoset-grid" data-layout="1">
